&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Boston ICT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lincolnshire Community Health Services NHS Trust is a vibrant and creative organisation which provides a diverse range of clinical services across Lincolnshire. Our Trust is proud to promote ‘The LCHS Way’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Integrated Team is excited to be advertising this opportunity for a development post of Band 6 Case Manager. This position is until September 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will provide exciting opportunities to develop and support the local Neighbourhood team. Successful candidates will be supported by their peers and team in driving forward improved patient care, self-management and reduce admissions to acute care. At the core of this role is working with the patient and their support networks across all parts of the health, social care and voluntary sector whether in their own home or care settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful you will ensure timely interventions, rehabilitation and management of long term and life limiting conditions. You will support hospital discharges and also facilitate onward referral to appropriate local services. The approach is to encourage self-management, anticipate changing needs and provide care planning for those patients requiring our service. You will be involved in some line management, supervision and training responsibilities within the ICT team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post includes weekends and bank holidays working flexibly to cover the needs of the service between 08 00 – 18 30hrs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
